  <description><![CDATA[<h2>Visit some of Switzerland's most iconic destinations on this popular multi-centre holiday</h2>
<p>Experience the best of Switzerland on this nine-night multi-centre holiday, designed to give you a true taste of this stunning country, including unforgettable experiences on two of the most spectacular panoramic journeys in the world: the Bernina and Glacier Express scenic trains. Discover the beautiful lakeside setting of <a data-udi="umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56819e7662924ccf91baa56999b5cbef}" title="Lucerne">Lucerne,</a> with its pedestrianised Old Town and nearby Mount Pilatus. Experience the world-famous St. Moritz, enjoy a day aboard the incredible Bernina Express and ride the Glacier Express panoramic train to the ‘Matterhorn village’ of <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/switzerland/zermatt">Zermatt</a>.</p>
<h3>Your multi-centre holiday options: </h3>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Nine nights in total with three nights in Lucerne, St. Moritz and Zermatt</li>
<li>Travel on a Wednesday and return home on a Friday from mid-June to the start of September</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<h3>Your holiday includes:</h3>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from UK</li>
<li>Swiss Half Fare Card - worth over £100 – included as part of your rail tickets</li>
<li>1st class rail transfers from Zurich or Geneva Airport to Lucerne, Lucerne to St. Moritz, St. Moritz to Zermatt (Glacier Express) and Zermatt to Zurich or Geneva Airport (some changes of train required)</li>
<li>Return day trip travel on the spectacular Bernina Express scenic train from St. Moritz to Tirano with seat reservations* - 1st class on the way there and 2nd class on the way back (the Bernina train line is shared between standard trains and panoramic trains with slightly larger windows, with various departure times throughout the day of each train type – your outward journey will be by panoramic train but due to demand, the return journey may be by standard train)</li>
<li>Travel on the famous Glacier Express train with seat reservation* as you journey from St Moritz to Zermatt. Lunch or a lunch box is included (catering service varies by train service) (some Glacier Express services start in Chur so the first part of your journey may be by standard train, followed by Glacier Express from Chur to Zermatt)</li>
<li>Free use of the mountain transport in St. Moritz included with your guest card from the hotel</li>
<li>Accommodation in your chosen hotel in each destination</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p><em>*Please note that we will organise seat reservations for you on the Bernina and Glacier Express but while we will try our very best to arrange seats together, due to huge demand on the services, we can’t guarantee this.</em></p>
